
Suppose you are working in a folder ~/mycode with a git rep

to add a repository in the same tree, say in 
/path/myCode.git

mkdir /path/myCode.git
cd /path/myCode.git
git --bare init 

cd ~/myCode

git remote add origin /path/myCode.git
git push origin master


now go to other machine

git clone ssh://user@host/path/myCode.git myCode

If you change someting in the other machine

#git push ssh://user@host/path/myCode.git 
git push 

use for fetching the latest changes 

git pull 

actually we I need to edit .git/config
and add the following

[alias] 
        mypull ssh://user@host/path/myCode.git


or

[alias] 
        mypull /path/myCode.git

